data.title: Peta Murgatroyd and Maksim Chmerkovskiy Welcome Third Baby and Reveal His Name
data.meta_description: The 'Dancing With the Stars' pros are now a family of five.
data.text:
The 'Dancing With the Stars' pros are now a family of five.

Fact checked by Sarah ScottFact checked by Sarah Scott

Dancing With the Stars pros Maksim Chmerkovskiy and Peta Murgatroyd are now parents of three and share that “the fam is complete.”

They announced via Instagram the birth of their little one, writing that the baby boy was born on July 12, 2024, at 8:48 a.m., weighing in at 8 pounds. They also revealed the tot’s name: Milan Maksim Chmerkovskiy.

Not only is the first name a famous city in Italy, but it’s a pretty popular one for babies in Europe, especially in the Czech Republic, the Netherlands, and Hungary. It's also becoming a bit more popular in America and was ranked 230th of all baby boy names in 2023, according to the Social Security Administration (SSA).

Here are all the baby name details:

Milan

Origin: Slavic

Meaning: This means gracious, dear; union according to go Nameberry.com.

Similar Names and Variations: Milo and Milani, or Paris and London when thinking of cities.

Famous Namesakes: This may be the name of a future athlete as several soccer players have it, including Milan Baroš, Milan Fukal, Milan Škriniar, and Milan Fryda.

Maksim

Origin: Latin

Meaning: This means greatest, according to go Nameberry.com.

Similar Names and Variations: Maxim, Maximo, Maximus

Famous Namesakes: Of course, the baby’s dad is a famous figure with this name, as well as soccer players Maksim Aleksandrovich Shatskikh and Maksim Medvedev.

This is the third son for the pair who are also parents to Shai, 7, and Rio, 1. They first met on Broadway in 2009 before becoming co-stars on DWTS. They tied the knot in 2017.

In a previous post, Chmerkovskiy said, “mom and baby are doing perfect, and delivery took around 47 seconds total! Exactly one push!”
